Final Report Analysis: Program Directors

Survey analysis output for cohorts 1 and 2 combined

Published

April 3, 2024

This html displays the key survey results for N = 20 program directors and staff. The table of contents on the left can be used to navigate across descriptive statistics categories.

Culturally Responsive Program Areas

  • In which of the following areas does the program at the [organization] offer employees or clients a culturally responsive treatment environment?
    • Organizational values
    • Governance
    • Client treatment planning
    • Evaluation and monitoring
    • Language service
    • Workforce and staff development
    • Organizational infrastructure
    • Other

The following table provides the count of respondents that endorsed having culturally responsive treatment environment for that particular program area. The most endorsed program area among coaches was organizational values (N = 20), and the least endorsed program area for culturally responsive environments was language service (N = 8).

# A tibble: 7 Ã 3
  Item                  Count Program_Areas                  
  <chr>                 <int> <chr>                          
1 cultural_responsive_1    18 Organizational values          
2 cultural_responsive_2    10 Governance                     
3 cultural_responsive_3    16 Client treatment planning      
4 cultural_responsive_4    17 Evaluation and monitoring      
5 cultural_responsive_5     8 Language service               
6 cultural_responsive_6    18 Workforce and staff development
7 cultural_responsive_7    15 Organizational infrastructure

Certification Requirement for Recovery Coaches

Our organization requires that recovery coaches are certified by the state of [org. state].

  • Yes/No/Other

Almost a quarter of our respondents did not respond to this survey item so results must be interpreted with caution. 41% of program directors reported that state certification was required for recovery coaches, while 36% reported that certification was not required.

  prc_certify n proportion CertificationRequired
1           1 9       0.45                   Yes
2           2 7       0.35                    No
3           3 2       0.10                 Other
4        <NA> 2       0.10          Missing Data

Frequency of Recovery Coachâs Contact with Individuals with SUDs

According to program directors, about the majority (90%) of recovery coaches interact with individuals with SUDs at least once/week.

  prc_interact  n proportion RC_Interaction_with_SUDs
1            1 15       0.75                    Daily
2            2  3       0.15               1+day/week
3            3  1       0.05            1-2days/month
4           NA  1       0.05             Missing Data

Program Experience

  • Program directors responded on a 5-point likert scale (Strongly disagree to strongly agree) for the following experiences with their programs:
  • My program has the organizational capacity needed to provide services
  • My program is able to leverage grant (i.e., financial) support
  • My program is able to collaborate with partners, organizations, and community resources
  • My program has received the support needed from AmeriCorps
  • The criminal history background check is problematic
  • The volunteer stipend is sufficient

The following graph summarizes the responses for each program experience.

Federal Opioid Development grant

Has your organization received funding or resources through the Federal Opioid Development grant?

55% of program directors reported that their organization has not received funding through the FOD grant.

  FOD_grant  n proportion FOD_grant_supported
1         1  8        0.4                 Yes
2         2 10        0.5                  No
3        NA  2        0.1        Missing Data

Monitoring and Oversight Plan

Does your program have a monitoring and oversight plan?

Most program directors (86%) reported having a monitoring and oversight plan.

  monitoring_plan  n proportion MonitoringPlan

Recovery Coach Recruitment

  • Program directors reported on the methods they used for recruiting recovery coaches:
  • Internal recovery program/ program graduates
  • Community recovery programs
  • Other community organizations
  • Schools and universities
  • Other

The following graph shows that alumn of internal programs (N = 13) are the most commonly reported source of recruited recovery coaches, while schools and universities (N = 4) are least commonly reported.

Lived Experience for Coaches

How important is it for a potential Peer Recovery Supporter to possess lived experience? The response choices were on a Likert Scale from 1- Very Important to 5- Very Unimportant. We had 5 missing responses, and N = 20 reported âVery Importantâ and only N = 1 reported âVery Unimportantâ. No program directors reported any other response option, so the program directors that provided a response felt strongly one way or another about lived experience for coaches.

  prc_livedexper  n proportion  LivedExperience
1              1 18       0.90   Very Important
2              5  1       0.05 Very Unimportant
3             NA  1       0.05     Missing Data
